# AgentCash — private agent guardrails (local only)

**Copy this file to `Private.md` at the repo root** and edit `Private.md`. The real `Private.md` is **gitignored** and never pushed to GitHub.  
**Do not put production secrets here** if you ever copy this file; use `.env.local` and Cloudflare/CI secret stores for keys.

---

## Product

- **Name:** AgentCash  
- **Repo:** monorepo (`apps/web`, `packages/mandate-engine`, MCP server, CLI, Supabase).

---

## Subdomains (maintain)

Official **AgentCash** host map — keep this table current when DNS, Workers, or Supabase redirect URLs change. Treat it as the source of truth for which hostname serves what.

| Hostname | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `agentcash.tech` | **Landing page** — marketing / public homepage |
| `app.agentcash.tech` | **Product** — this repo’s Next.js app (dashboard, approvals UI, webhooks today) |
| `api.agentcash.tech` | **APIs** — agent REST (`/api/v1/*`), webhooks, programmatic entry (may route to the same Worker as `app` initially, or a dedicated Worker later) |
| `docs.agentcash.tech` | **Docs** — product & developer documentation site |
| `auth.agentcash.tech` | **Auth** — login / SSO / Supabase Auth callbacks when split from the main app |
| `status.agentcash.tech` | **Status page** — uptime & incident comms |

**Env:** set `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL`, `APPROVAL_BASE_URL`, and OAuth/magic-link callback URLs to the **canonical** origins you expose (often `https://app.agentcash.tech` until `api` / `auth` are isolated on their own hostnames).

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  L["agentcash.tech (landing)"]
  P["app.agentcash.tech (product)"]
  A["api.agentcash.tech (APIs)"]
  D["docs.agentcash.tech (docs)"]
  U["auth.agentcash.tech (auth)"]
  S["status.agentcash.tech (status)"]
  L --> P
  P -.-> A
  U -.-> P
```

